26/11/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium – Romanian European Integration Minister Alexandru Farcas was in Brussels on Thursday (25 November) attending the EU-Romania Association Committee meeting. 
He outlined the latest developments related to EU accession, ahead of the 17 December summit. 
Farcas says Romania remains hopeful that EU entry on 1 January 2007 would be confirmed. 
"There are further positive macroeconomic developments in our country and, for the first time … there is also progress in the public administration and judiciary reform," he said. 
(Rompres- 25/11/04)
